title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3090B3807F274E5CA17E2E7590EB1CC0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare U-251MG single cell suspension at the desired seeding concentration. Cells can be from freshly prepared culture or from frozen vials in liquid nitrogen. Frozen vials can be immediately thawed using 37\u00b0C waterbath and maintained in Nunclon Delta T25 cell culture flask with complete medium (Dulbecco's Modified Eagle Medium (DMEM) supplemented with 10% V\/V Fetal Bovine Serum (FBS) + 1% vol. of 100mM Penicillin-Streptomycin for 1 passage before seeding for spheroid generation.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138315,"guid":"C21A6B207CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138314,"previous_guid":"C218BD707CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"21A6C594CA9D422FA85D56AA7F646559","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"01EBA7922468481A82E82D54CF31DD25","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Once flasks are 70-80% confluent, medium from the flask is aspirated and U-251 MG tumor cell monolayers are washed with 1X phosphate buffered saline (PBS; 5 ml for a 25 cm2 or 8 - 10 ml for a 75 cm2 flask), add 0.25 X Trypsin-EDTA cell dissociation enzyme (2 ml for a 25 cm2 or 4 ml for a 75 cm2 flask) and incubate cells at 37 \u00b0C for 2 - 5 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138316,"guid":"C21C3FE07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138315,"previous_guid":"C21A6B207CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"55DEBD4C751345BC945E25DAD8741866","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D8A2375AC8A1473991AF5F6E9CA570DF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Check cell detachment under a microscope and neutralize cell dissociation enzyme with complete growth medium.The  0.25 X Trypsin-EDTA reagent is neutralized using 4 volumes of complete medium<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138317,"guid":"C21E14A07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138316,"previous_guid":"C21C3FE07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F358008372BC48DB988C67C9041E0662","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C6883D837BD9497BB95D67BE43468C15","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge U-251 MG single cell suspension at 5000rpm for 5 min, remove supernatant, tap the tube and re-suspend cell pellet in complete growth medium using a pipette. This should yield a single cell suspension without cell clusters.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138318,"guid":"C22085A07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138317,"previous_guid":"C21E14A07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"13B0278394DD4F72AB325C003BC5327E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"71463F4772D841C3B0B4F8EC34B1521D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Cells with a viability >90% can be used for spheroid generation. Mix 10\u00b5l of cells with 10\u00b5l of Trypan Blue and count cells using a haemocytometer.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138319,"guid":"C222F6A07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138318,"previous_guid":"C22085A07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"93438120CA9948069CD7758A14CEB608","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1F8AD18291E14FA49CB7A65ACDB5DC6A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Calculated cell seeding density. Prepare a suitable volume of each cell seeding density to dispense the correct volume per well multiplied by the number of wells at each cell concentration.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138320,"guid":"C225B5C07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138319,"previous_guid":"C222F6A07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"26C4399B81B342258F30E1E15F6EBBE0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0110F5D022AC437E96B2CA8BA7223C86","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the cell suspension to a sterile reservoir and dispense 200 \u03bcl\/well into ultra-low attachment 96-well plates usinga multichannel pipette ensuring pipette tips do not touch the surface of the wells to protect surface coating<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138321,"guid":"C2289BF07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138320,"previous_guid":"C225B5C07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"98EBFA59EFA5484D8B0241795EA9472A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"888EACDD2EFE475283C72DE85D310BC9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge the Nunclon\u2122 Sphera\u2122 96-Well plates at 1250rpm for 5 minutes and transfer the plates to an incubator (37 \u00b0C, 5% CO2, 95% humidity).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138322,"guid":"C22C1E607CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138321,"previous_guid":"C2289BF07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"03598DD98D244C06A1E9967FC6D607F6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8228AF21F3A74AE9A7BE221C1856F3A4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After 24h incubation, the media must be replenished. Remove 100\u03bcl media without disrupting tumorspheres and add 100\u03bcl of fresh media (DMEM + 10%FBS + 1%Ab) into each well and incubate at 37\u00b0C (5% CO2, 95% humidity). The sides of wells should be used to remove or add media and pipetting should be carried out at average or below average speeds to avoid disruption to spheroids<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138323,"guid":"C23016007CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138322,"previous_guid":"C22C1E607CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3DAC54AE795B45B39865B79269506551","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AA82DAAC4BB54C14B35DF4A49E4E9942","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">U-251 MG Human glioblastoma astrocytoma spheroids will usually form in 3-7 days  from the starting date depending on seeding density and visually confirm tumor spheroid formation daily using Bright-field microscope.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1138324,"guid":"C23482D07CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","previous_id":1138323,"previous_guid":"C23016007CDD11EB82E1F796DC1CC8E2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"078A5BFED58D403CA10EDB1C2FA629CE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8E1C53D4449F4D4C87901AAB27FEE99B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Imaging and quantification of spheroids can be also be monitored in situ using a cytometer and fluorescent live cell stains<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>3D cell culture is a process used to grow cells <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vitro <\/span><span>to mimic an <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vivo <\/span><span>environment. 3D cell models are very useful for understanding disease mechanisms and exploring drug therapeutics. 3D cultures can be grown from cells taken from cancer organoids in patients. Once grown, they can be used to screen for small molecule drugs or they can be genetically modified in order to analyse disease pathways or predict the toxicity or efficacy of a drug treatment. These cultures decrease the need to use animals in research and provides more reliable results as it uses human physiology. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol describes the <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vitro <\/span><span>generation of spheroids using the low attachment plate method. This method uses low-adhesion plates that are coated with hydrophilic polymer to allow cells to cluster together, forming their own extracellular matrix, rather than sticking to the plate surface. The scaffold-free 3D cell culture models produced can more accurately reflect an <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vivo <\/span><span>microenvironment making them useful in the study of oncology, hepatotoxicity, neurology, nephrology and stem cell biology. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">A<\/span><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/df8ybifip.jpg\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">B<\/span><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/df84bifip.jpg\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">We used low attachment plates for tumorsphere construction and plates from Thermo Fisher Scientific and adapted protocols published by: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1. Perkinelmer.com. 2021. [online] Available at: <https:\/\/www.perkinelmer.com\/lab-solutions\/resources\/docs\/gde_3d_culture_user_guide.pdf> [Accessed 18 February 2021].<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2. Thermofisher.com. 2021. HepG2 Cell Line Spheroid Generation and Characterization for HT Assays | Thermo Fisher Scientific - UK. [online] Available at: <https:\/\/www.thermofisher.com\/ie\/en\/home\/references\/protocols\/cell-culture\/3-d-cell-culture-protocol\/hepg2-cell-line-spheroid-generation.html> [Accessed 18 February 2021].<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/df88bifip.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1620215305}